---
import FrameworkLayout from '../../layouts/FrameworkLayout.astro';
import { url } from '../../utils';

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "MedicalWebPage",
  "name": "Phase 2: Preparation — Hospital Acupuncture Implementation",
  "description": "Develop strategies to leverage enablers and address barriers before implementing acupuncture or acupressure in a hospital setting.",
  "url": "https://hospitalacupuncture.com/framework/preparation/",
  "lastReviewed": "2026-04",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Dr Zhen Zheng",
    "affiliation": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "RMIT University" }
  }
};
---

<FrameworkLayout
  title="Preparation"
  description="Develop strategies to use enablers and address barriers identified in Phase 1."
  phaseNumber={2}
  bottomLine="In this phase, the team turns Phase 1 findings into actionable plans: selecting the right intervention, determining timing, identifying suitable patient groups, revising hospital guidelines, and assigning clear roles. Thorough preparation is what separates a successful rollout from a stalled pilot."
  schema={schema}
>

  <p>
    In this Phase, the team will develop strategies to use enablers and address barriers
    identified in Phase 1.
  </p>

  <h3>Key Phase 2 Items</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Identify appropriate timing for acupuncture/acupressure intervention</li>
    <li>Revise or update hospital guidelines</li>
    <li>Identify and revise relevant documents</li>
    <li>Determine each team member's role (using CFIR framework)</li>
    <li>Define suitable patient types and surgical procedures</li>
    <li>Address identified barriers</li>
    <li>Determine intervention delivery personnel based on timing</li>
  </ul>

  <nav class="section-nav">
    <p><strong>Select any of the following categories to continue:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#feasibility">Feasibility of the Selected Intervention</a></li>
      <li><a href="#time-point">Identify the Time Point for Introducing Acupuncture</a></li>
      <li><a href="#types-of-patients">Types of Patients and Surgery</a></li>
      <li><a href="#hospital-guidelines">Hospital Guidelines and Documentation</a></li>
      <li><a href="#address-barriers">Address Barriers</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <!-- Feasibility -->
  <h2 id="feasibility">Feasibility of the Selected Intervention</h2>

  <details open>
    <summary>FAME Criteria</summary>
    <p>
      References the FAME criteria (Feasibility, Appropriateness, Meaningfulness, Effectiveness)
      developed by Pearson et al. (2005).
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Feasibility:</strong> Can it be done in this setting with available resources?</li>
      <li><strong>Appropriateness:</strong> Does it fit the clinical context and patient population?</li>
      <li><strong>Meaningfulness:</strong> Is it valued by patients and clinicians?</li>
      <li><strong>Effectiveness:</strong> Does the evidence support clinical benefit?</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Assessment concludes that "acupressure is a feasible, appropriate, meaningful and effective
      intervention that should be implemented for PONV."
    </p>
  </details>

  <!-- Timing -->
  <h2 id="time-point">Identify the Time Point for Introducing Acupuncture</h2>

  <details open>
    <summary>Timing Considerations</summary>
    <p>
      Intervention timing depends on purpose: prevention requires pre-operative or immediate
      post-operative application, while management occurs after symptoms appear.
    </p>
    <p>
      Acupuncture is "often provided 30 min prior to surgery" or potentially 12&ndash;24 hours
      beforehand, with timing influenced by staff availability and surgical scheduling.
    </p>
  </details>

  <!-- Patient Selection -->
  <h2 id="types-of-patients">Types of Patients and Surgery</h2>

  <details open>
    <summary>Patient Risk Factors</summary>
    <p>High-risk PONV indicators include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Female gender</li>
      <li>Prior PONV or motion sickness history</li>
      <li>Non-smoker status</li>
      <li>Younger age</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Surgery types with elevated risk include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Cholecystectomy</li>
      <li>Gynecological procedures</li>
      <li>Laparoscopic procedures</li>
    </ul>
  </details>

  <!-- Documentation -->
  <h2 id="hospital-guidelines">Hospital Guidelines and Documentation</h2>

  <details open>
    <summary>Implementation Requirements</summary>
    <p>
      Integrating acupuncture or acupressure into hospital practice typically requires:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Hospital PONV guidelines revision</li>
      <li>PONV checklists</li>
      <li>Patient education materials</li>
      <li>Operative and ward documentation updates</li>
      <li>Drug chart modifications</li>
    </ul>
  </details>

  <!-- Barriers -->
  <h2 id="address-barriers">Address Barriers</h2>

  <details open>
    <summary>Primary Barriers Identified</summary>
    <p>Four key obstacles:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Lack of awareness regarding existing evidence</li>
      <li>Insufficient capability</li>
      <li>Equipment unavailability</li>
      <li>Time constraints</li>
    </ol>
  </details>

  <!-- Downloads -->
  <div class="downloads">
    <h3>Phase 2 Resources</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><a href={url('/resources/')}>FAME criteria assessment template</a></li>
      <li><a href={url('/resources/')}>Sample hospital guideline revision checklist</a></li>
      <li><a href={url('/resources/')}>Barrier-strategy mapping worksheet</a></li>
      <li><a href={url('/resources/')}>Team role assignment template (CFIR-based)</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

</FrameworkLayout>
